description: Ready in 2 steps, this super-easy zucchini slice is the perfect veg-packed dinner. It's transports easily, making it a great next-day lunch choice.
name: Grandma’s zucchini slice Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 4 middle bacon rashers, fat trimmed, diced

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 160°C/180°C fan-forced. Lightly grease a 26cm (5cm deep) round ceramic pie dish. Lightly beat eggs in a large bowl. Add oil and stir to combine. Add zucchini, carrot, potato, onion, bacon and flour, then stir well to combine. Season with pepper.
Pour mixture into dish. Bake for 50 minutes or until golden and set. Cool in dish for 5 minutes. Slice and serve.
